title: VEHICLE USAGE PATTERN EVALUATION
summary: <SOH> BRIEF DESCRIPTION OF THE DRAWINGS <EOH>FIG. 1 illustrates an example computing device in communication with a mobile device for receiving vehicle usage data. FIG. 2 is a block diagram showing example components of the computing device of FIG. 1 . FIG. 3 is a map showing example vehicle usage data and an example cluster based on the usage date. FIG. 4 is a flowchart of an example process that may be executed by the computing device to cluster vehicle users according to the vehicle usage data. detailed-description description="Detailed Description" end="lead"?
abstract: A computing device includes a processing circuit and a data storage medium. The processing circuit is programmed to receive first vehicle usage data associated with a first user and second vehicle usage data associated with a second user. The processing device can identify a first pattern associated with the first vehicle usage data, identify a second pattern associated with the second vehicle usage data, and determine whether the first pattern is complementary to the second pattern.
